AD  - Unidad Educativa Municipal Cayambe, Cayambe, Ecuador
AB  - The main purpose of this research is to apply the 4PADAFE Methodology so that teachers can develop their digital skills. Educators have to develop 21st century digital skills to improve their didactic practice and innovate their classes in all kind of modalities of study. Educational institutions, faced with the new demands of the knowledge and information society, have to head towards the transformation of new teaching and learning models. The theoretical foundations of the methodology proposed are behaviourism, cognitivism, constructivism, and connectivism as a transversal axis in a flipped classroom and student-based learning context. The importance of the methodology lies in the fact that, being a comprehensive methodology, it encompasses pedagogical, methodological and technological components as well as didactic strategies, focusing on developing digital skills. In order to reach the objectives established in this research project, surveys were applied on teachers from different educational institutions and, consequently, a quantitative analysis of the digital skills proposed by this methodology was carried out. As main findings, it is evident that the 4PADAFE Methodology contributed to developing digital skills in teachers through the accompaniment in the systematic process that guided the development and construction of a massive virtual classroom. © 2023, The Author(s), under exclusive license to Springer Nature Singapore Pte Ltd.
